    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Manual Door Opener</title>
        <para>The manual passenger entry door opener (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47006108">Fig. 108</hotlnk>) is an option that may be required by the state or local
            municipality. The manual door opener assembly control handle (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47006109">Fig. 109, Item 7</hotlnk>) is located at the right wing switch panel. The door
            opener transverse rod is situated along the step well and attaches to the door at a mid level height.
        </para>
        <figure id="f47006108" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="224px"/>
            <caption>Figure 108. Manual Door Opener Operating Handle</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BUS KEY IGNITION SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DEFROSTER DUCT (ENTRY PANEL REMOVED FOR DETAIL)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. DOOR OPENER SLIDE ROD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>4. FORWARD PASSENGER DOOR PANEL</callout1>
                <callout1>5. DOOR CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                <callout1>6. MANUAL DOOR OPENER ASSEMBLY SUPPORT LEG</callout1>
                <callout1>7. MANUAL DOOR OPENER HANDLE AND CUT OUT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f47006109" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006109.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="240px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 109. Manual Door Opener Transverse Control Rod</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RIGHT WING PANEL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ENTRY DEFROST DUCT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. DOOR CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                <callout1>4. WING PANEL AND DOOR OPENER SUPPORT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. MANUAL DOOR OPENER HANDLE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
